# scratch-repack + arg-repoint of func_80082380 (static path) caused sprite
# flicker and did NOT extend the visible band. Conclusions:
# 1. func_80082380 serves MULTIPLE callers (func_80082CFC/2E04/2F10) whose
#    buffers are NOT all 7x10 backdrop grids — repacking every call corrupts
#    the non-backdrop draws (=> flicker). Any future hook must discriminate
#    by caller/buffer address (e.g. only repack when ctx->r7 matches known
#    backdrop arrays) or patch a backdrop-specific wrapper instead.
# 2. The in-level treeline band the user sees is most likely drawn by the
#    SCROLLING path (func_80082820, buffer arg = $a0/ctx->r4 per the
#    func_80082F10 call site) — the deferred one. Start there next time,
#    with per-caller buffer identification FIRST (log ctx args + buffer
